The paper discusses the performance of spatially coupled LDPC codes in the context of channel coding and transmission over parallel channels. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of belief propagation decoding, which is a common technique in coding theory and signal processing, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), or Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-categories.
